entry.title: Reland "[Layout] Remove hintAtTabSelection from startHiding"
entry.content:
This reverts commit 2d0e0250a2a204dacde2e6b88e7d91c7eda51495.



This was reverted previously because ActivityTabProvider had a

onTabSelectionHintedObserver and the previous CL failed to clean up

the observer method leading to this being missed. This resulted in a

visual issue where the TabCount could be seen



ActivityTabProvider had a test for this, but the timing was too loose.

The tab was eventually selected correctly, but it was after the animation finished and not before (see https://crbug.com/1498377).

Unfortunately, I'm not sure there is a way to tighten the timing of the

test because animations are off in tests so testing this intermediate

timing is difficult if not impossible...



This CL relands the change after properly removing the remaining observers of hintAtTabSelection. This required updating Start surface

and tab switcher layouts to select a tab before the transition happens

and we can then observe that in ActivityTabProvider to get around the removal of hintAtTabSelection.



Note that it was found this sequencing could result in stack overflow

due to start surface and the tab switcher not expecting a tab

switch to occur while they were visible without triggering another

onTabSelecting call. This is easy enough to fix by preventing

onTabSelecting from being re-entered while the selection is not yet finished.



In a follow-up CL I will remove the tabId from startHiding as well.

entry.title: [omnibox][actions] Fix deduplicated starter pack matches via preference
entry.content:
This CL fixes the bug where starter pack matches could disappear while

typing the keyword, e.g. "@bookmarks", when the user has bookmarked

the starter pack destination. chrome://bookmarks can itself be

bookmarked, and then the bookmark would be preferred, thus disrupting

the keyword user experience by deduplicating the starter pack match.

Preferring starter pack matches isn't enough, as upgrading the match

with duplicate info could corrupt the contents with unrelated text

about the bookmark (that it's in "Other bookmarks", for example). So

the provider preference is also set equal to bookmarks to keep the

original match intact.

entry.title: Support leading attr for TextViewWithLeading in TextAppearances.
entry.content:
This was accomplished by resolving the applicable TextAppearance

manually and checking for a leading inside of it.



As part of this change, all TextAppearances that contained a

android:textSize were updated to also contain a leading attr. This can

be done at the TextAppearance level because there's an exact 1:1

mapping between android:textSize and leading values. And to prevent

future misuse, added an assert in TextViewWithLeading to verify the

leading attr is present.



Some existing usage of TextViewWithLeading was missing TextAppearance

and leading values. When tests encountered issues, this CL also

updated layouts and render test revs for the changes in this CL.



However it's still likely that some sites do not have sufficient test

coverage and were missed. To guard against causing potential issues,

added a //ui/ kill switch as well to turn off the assert/crash portion

of this change.



Future changes will remove previous non-TextAppearance leading values

and add a PRESUBMIT against vanilla TextViews. No current plans to

wholesale migrate all existing TextView usage.

entry.title: Enable WAL mode for DIPS database
entry.content:
This CL is switching the journal mode of DIPS database to use

WAL (Write-Ahead Logging). Instead of using a journal file

which contains a rollback with the original data (database-journal),

the database will have a Write-Ahead Logging which contains the modifications. Modifications are merge into the original on a snapshot.



see: Write-Ahead Logging (https://www.sqlite.org/wal.html)



The main advantage of using WAL is a reduction in the amount

of disk flushes by SQL write.





Important notes on the DIPS database:



[*] Databases can safely be opened in any mode; and open back

later in with a different journal mode.

see: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/5019145



[*] The DIPS database doesn't use SQL Recovery.



[*] The DIPS database is open in exclusive mode. WAL doesn't

requires to use Share Memory for the wal-index



[*] Errors related to opening a WAL database can be tracked

with the UMA metric: Privacy.DIPS.DatabaseInit

entry.title: [iOS] Fix unresponsive NTP scrolling with container
entry.content:
Feed container constraints would lock when the header reached the

bottom of the NTP, preventing the NTP from being scrollable. This was

because the container had an anchor to the top of the header and to the

bottom of the view, which would eventually overlap and break.



Instead of anchoring the container to the bottom of the view, we use a height anchor that's updated whenever the feed's content is changed.

entry.title: Move //content/browser/renderer_host/input/synthetic_gesture_controller
entry.content:
to //content/common/input



This change adds task_runner as an argument to constructor of class

SyntheticGestureController to remove dependency on browser_thread.h and

moves it into //content/common/input. This change also pull other

synthetic input related files into //content/common/input.



This refactoring is a part of bigger project to handle input on viz

thread (go/input-on-viz). We are moving input related interfaces that

RenderWidgetHostImpl uses to //content/common/input. This would provide

a single stack in //content/common/input that we quickly enter in either

the browser or GPU viz which would allow for relatively clean movement

of code. GPU process can link in the same input stack and forward the

data to the renderer using the same code.

entry.title: Revert "webview: shut down old cookie store after switch."
entry.content:
This reverts commit eaab6a16d1bd941536f6ae9729ec3c9bc407dfc1.



Reason for revert: crbug/1505868



Original change's description:

> webview: shut down old cookie store after switch.

>

> When switching from the temporary cookie store (used when CookieManager

> is required before Chromium has been initialised) to the Mojo cookie

> store that's used under normal operation, shut down the cookie store

> once we've flushed it so that it closes the SQLite database properly,

> and shut down the backend thread it was using to execute store jobs.

>

> Also, lazily create the backend thread, as it's not needed in the case

> where we don't create the temporary store in the first place.

>

> The client thread is used by CookieManager in both implementations, so

> its behaviour is not changed.

>

entry.title: Revert "Check if math expression has percentages deep inside"
entry.content:
This reverts commit fc365dddd74a2c9ba22036fd5563dbea8ff34c7c.

> Check if math expression has percentages deep inside

>

> Currently, only the top level category is checked to have a percentage

> dependency, check all the nodes inside the expression as well,

> as it can be the case like:

> NumberProducingFunction(Percentage) * Pixels.

> The top level category is Length in such case and we try to resolve it

> with ComputeLength, where percentages are not allowed.
